Week plan — realistic for 1 week
Day 1 — setup + summarization

Create the project in VSCode, init git repo
Build the file upload + text input in Streamlit
Connect facebook/bart-large-cnn or flan-t5-large for summarization
Push to GitHub

Day 2 — action items extraction

Use a flan-t5 prompt like: "Extract action items and responsible people from this meeting transcript"
Display results as a clean checklist in Streamlit
Test with sample transcripts

Day 3 — sentiment analysis

Connect your sentiment model from your mini-projet (you already built this!)
Analyze sentiment per speaker turn, not just the whole meeting
Show a small bar chart in Streamlit (you know how to do this with matplotlib)

Day 4 — RAG Q&A feature

Reuse your exact RAG code from mini-projet (chunking, FAISS, flan-t5)
Add a text input in Streamlit: "Ask a question about this meeting"
Show the answer + which part of the transcript it came from

Day 5 — polish + integration

Connect all 4 tabs into one clean Streamlit app
Handle edge cases (empty file, transcript too short)
Write a proper README with screenshots

Day 6 — testing + GitHub

Test with 3-4 different sample transcripts
Fix any bugs
Push final version to GitHub with a clean commit history

Day 7 — buffer

Add anything you didn't finish
Or add one bonus feature (speaker identification, keyword extraction)